REPOSITORY

The main foursquared repo is at http://joelapenna.com/git/foursquared.git

*Some files must be manually created in order for the tests and source to build.*

*Create res/values/credentials.xml* -- do not check this in. It must contain strings:

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<resources>
  <string
    name="google_maps_api_key">SOME_TEST_KEY</string>

  <string
    name="oauth_consumer_key">SOME_OTHER_KEY</string>
  <string
    name="oauth_consumer_secret">SOME_OTHER_OTHER_KEY</string>
</resources>

*Create src/com/joelapenna/foursquare/test/TestConstants.java* -- do not check this in. It must contain strings:
   
public class TestConstants {

    static final String oAuthConsumerKey = "SOME_OTHER_KEY";
    static final String oAuthConsumerSecret = "SOME_OTHER_OTHER_KEY";

    static final String testFoursquareUsername = "testuser@example.com";
    static final String testFoursquarePassword = "some_password";
}

IDEAS

+ "Lead" a Bar Crawl
Use your phone to generate a "proxy" authentication credentials and store that on your client. Pass that authentication credential onto another phone, maybe by QRCode and allow others to act on your behalf. Provide UI on your phone to disable that credential by sending an RPC to /api/logout with those credentials.

This will give a user the ability to designate someone else as their notifier. This allows people to form up for a bar crawl, with one person leading the checkins for foursquare.

+ Shortcuts to favorite checkins.

+ Yelp Integration

+ Send all venue opens to the query suggest provider, provide a quick search interface.


TODO

+ Display tags for a venue.


-------------
URL for location suggestion provider.
curl 'http://playfoursquare.com/venues?q=pie&cityid=23'

+ CHECKIN Example
http://m.playfoursquare.com/checkin?privacy=0&security_token=&shout=&twitter=0&venue=Noc+Noc

-- Request Headers
